msgid "Vague, confusing, rambling, or incomplete challenge descriptions."
msgstr "模糊、令人困惑、冗长或不完整的挑战描述。"

#: src/impact-and-results/learners-at-our-university.md:17
msgid ""
"Residual hard-to-bridge conceptual gaps between some of the challenges, with "
"data piping (between processes), file globbing, symbolic links, and the "
"security implications of the PATH environment variable specifically "
"mentioned."
msgstr ""
"一些挑战之间残留的难以弥合的概念差距，特别提到了数据管道（进程之间）、文件通配、符号链接以及 PATH 环境变量的安全含义。"

#: src/impact-and-results/learners-at-our-university.md:18
msgid ""
"Overly-repetitive challenge ramps (e.g., too much practice for concepts such "
"as chmod)."
msgstr ""
"过于重复的挑战斜坡（例如，对 chmod 等概念练习过多）。"

#: src/impact-and-results/learners-at-our-university.md:20
msgid ""
"Anecdotally, we found that the introduction of the Linux Luminarium during "
"the 2024-2025 academic year drastically improved student understanding of "
"Linux throughout the rest of the course. Whereas prior iterations of this "
"course would receive introductory questions from students (e.g., about the "
"Linux filesystem layout, the Linux process model, etc.), we observed almost "
"no such questions in either semester that included the Linux Luminarium."
msgstr ""
"根据轶事，我们发现 2024-2025 学年引入 Linux Luminarium 极大地改善了学生在课程其余部分对 Linux 的理解。虽然之前版本的课程会收到学生的入门问题（例如，关于 Linux 文件系统布局、Linux 进程模型等），但在包含 Linux Luminarium 的两个学期中，我们几乎没有观察到此类问题。"

#: src/impact-and-results/learners-at-our-university.md:22
msgid ""
"Consent or lack thereof had no impact on grades or other student metrics in "
"the class."
msgstr ""
"同意或缺乏同意对班级的成绩或其他学生指标没有影响。"

#: src/impact-and-results/community-involvement.md:3
msgid ""
"Because the Linux Luminarium is openly available and open source, and the "
"material is intentionally very introductory, passionate learners are able to "
"contribute to the project. Over the roughly 14 months of its availability, "
"we have received contributions from 15 distinct individuals from the global "
"community. These contributions ranged from spelling and grammar fixes to "
"entire sub-modules of content. For example, the Linux Luminarium's file "
"permissions module was initially contributed by a community member."
msgstr ""
"因为 Linux Luminarium 是公开可用和开源的，并且材料有意设计得非常入门，热情的学习者能够为项目做出贡献。在其可用的大约 14 个月中，我们收到了来自全球社区的 15 个不同个人的贡献。这些贡献范围从拼写和语法修复到整个内容子模块。例如，Linux Luminarium 的文件权限模块最初是由社区成员贡献的。"

#: src/conclusion.md:3
msgid ""
"The Linux Luminarium is a novel, turnkey, challenge-based Linux education "
"platform that supercharges learners to become proficient Linux users. Over "
"the year of its open availability, the Linux Luminarium has taught Linux to "
"15,394 learners, shepherding them through solving 697,553 challenges. By "
"surveying learners around the country as well as at our University, we show "
"that the Linux Luminarium, and the techniques that underpin it, successfully "
"drive student learning. The Linux Luminarium is both openly available on the "
"internet for turnkey learning and open source to enable reproducibility, "
"learning, and ongoing research."
msgstr ""
"Linux Luminarium 是一个新颖的、开箱即用的、基于挑战的 Linux 教育平台，它能够增强学习者的能力，使他们成为熟练的 Linux 用户。在其开放可用的一年中，Linux Luminarium 已向 15,394 名学习者教授 Linux，引导他们解决了 697,553 个挑战。通过调查全国各地的学习者以及我们大学的学习者，我们表明 Linux Luminarium 及其支撑技术成功地推动了学生学习。Linux Luminarium 既在互联网上公开可用以进行开箱即用的学习，也是开源的，以实现可重现性、学习和持续研究。"

